The body of a 27-year-old man was recovered, this morning (2 November) by members from Port Shepstone Search and Rescue and K9 Search and Rescue. The members were called out to Mgai area, Sawoti, in the South Coast for a missing person. It is alleged that a 27-year-old man was brutally beaten to death and then rolled down the side of the hill.  K9 Bear was utilised to search the area and positively located the body of the missing person. The hill was 70m downhill. A high angle rope system was set up and lowered members down to the body. The body was bagged and secured in a stokes rescue basket and hauled up to the roadway and handed over to Sawoti detectives on scene. A case of murder is being investigated by police.